In The Age Of Legalization, Talking To Kids About Marijuana Gets Tougher

    Facebook
    Twitter
    Flipboard
    Email

November 10, 2017 5:01 AM ET

Anna Gorman

From Kaiser Health News
Enlarge this image

Kids who saw an ad for legal marijuana were more likely to report smoking it one year later, according to a Rand Corp. report. Tomas Rodriguez/Getty Images hide caption
toggle caption
Tomas Rodriguez/Getty Images

Kids who saw an ad for legal marijuana were more likely to report smoking it one year later, according to a Rand Corp. report.
